Officers were patrolling in the area when they saw a Mazda vehicle reportedly involved in a murder earlier. An unknown man was found about 2.45am yesterday with multiple stab wounds in an open field next to the De Nova Youth Treatment Centre, old Paarl road, Kraaifontein. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said the witnesses saw four suspects fleeing the crime scene in a white Mazda 323. “Community of Kraaifontein participated in partnership policing when they shared valuable information with the police about suspects that were involved in a murder. “Police followed up on the information and spotted the vehicle and, upon searching it, they found a knife that was allegedly used in the murder and four occupants inside the vehicle,” she said. She said the two men would appear in the Blue Down Magistrate’s Court once they have been charged. Cape Times